The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and Chancellor Merkel during a bilateral meeting at the G20 summit in Buenos Aires. They discussed various topics including trade, defense, Ukraine, Syria, and the violations of the INF treaty by Russia. President Trump also mentioned his condolences to the Bush family following the passing of former President George H.W. Bush, and canceled a planned press conference out of respect. He confirmed that he will still be meeting with President Xi of China to discuss trade.